<subSubSection id="24CB1080FFADFFF3FAB2ABAA823FFA1A" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="6C6E430BFFADFFF3FAB2ABAA825AFA76" blockId="25.[151,1437,932,1427]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFADFFF3FAB2ABAA815EFB3A" bold="true" box="[199,315,1220,1246]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Remarks.</emphasis>
Previous records from the coast of São Paulo include Ubatuba, Caraguatatuba, Ilha Vitória, Santos, and Guarujá (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFADFFF3FB58AB8682E8FAE6" author="Severino-Rodrigues, E. &amp; Hebling, N. J. &amp; Graca-Lopes, R." box="[301,653,1256,1282]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="171 - 182" refId="ref78241" refString="Severino-Rodrigues, E., Hebling, N. J. &amp; Graca-Lopes, R. (2007) Biodiversidade no produto da pesca de arrasto-de-fundo dirigida ao lagostim, Metanephrops rubellus (Moreira, 1903), desembarcado no litoral do estado de Sao Paulo, Brasil. Boletim do Instituto de Pesca, 33 (2), 171 - 182." type="journal article" year="2007">
Severino-Rodrigues 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFADFFF3F860AB878228FAE6" box="[533,589,1256,1282]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFADFFF3F8EDAB868335FAE6" author="Dall'Occo, P. L." box="[664,848,1256,1282]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refId="ref60273" refString="Dall'Occo, P. L. (2010) Taxonomia e Distribuicao das Lagostas (Crustacea: Decapoda: Achelata e Polychelida) no Oceano Atlantico. PhD Thesis (unpublished), Universidade Estadual Paulista (Unesp), Rio Claro, 432 pp." type="book" year="2010">Dall’Occo 2010</bibRefCitation>
). According to 
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFADFFF3F982AB8784DAFAE6" author="Yang, C. H. &amp; Bracken-Grissom, H. &amp; Kim, D. &amp; Crandall, K. A. &amp; Chan, T. Y." box="[1015,1215,1256,1283]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="237 - 250" refId="ref82678" refString="Yang, C. H., Bracken-Grissom, H., Kim, D., Crandall, K. A. &amp; Chan, T. Y. (2012) Phylogenetic relationships, character evolution, and taxonomic implications within the slipper lobsters (Crustacea: Decapoda: Scyllaridae). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 62 (1), 237 - 250. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2011.09.019" type="journal article" year="2012">
Yang 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFADFFF3FE42AB87840BFAE6" box="[1079,1134,1256,1282]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
(2012)
</bibRefCitation>
the genus 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFADFFF3FF41AB868122FAC3" authority="Fabricius, 1775" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" class="Malacostraca" family="Scyllaridae" genus="Scyllarus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFADFFF3FF41AB8685F9FAE6" box="[1332,1436,1256,1282]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Scyllarus</emphasis>
Fabricius, 1775
</taxonomicName>
is paraphyletic. This species is not specially fished for economic interest (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFADFFF3FEE0AA628559FAC2" author="Holthuis, L. B." box="[1173,1340,1292,1318]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 292" refId="ref64998" refString="Holthuis, L. B. (1991) Marine lobsters of the world. An annotated and illustrated catalogue of species of interest to fisheries known to date. FAO Fisheries Synopsis, 125 (13), 1 - 292." type="journal article" year="1991">Holthuis 1991</bibRefCitation>
). This is very abundant in São Paulo coast and it is captured as bycatch of pink shrimp (
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFADFFF3FE7EAA5E8534FAAE" baseAuthorityName="Latreille" baseAuthorityYear="1817" box="[1035,1361,1328,1354]" class="Malacostraca" family="Penaeidae" genus="Farfantepenaeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFADFFF3FE7EAA5E8534FAAE" box="[1035,1361,1328,1354]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Farfantepenaeus brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFADFFF3FFFDAA5F8164FA8A" baseAuthorityName="Perez Farfante" baseAuthorityYear="1967" class="Malacostraca" family="Penaeidae" genus="Farfantepenaeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paulensis">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFADFFF3FFFDAA5F8164FA8A" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">F. paulensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFADFFF3FB6FAA3A8268FA8A" author="Keunecke, K. A. &amp; Vianna M. &amp; Fonseca, D. B. &amp; D'Incao, F." box="[282,525,1364,1390]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="49 - 55" refId="ref66020" refString="Keunecke, K. A., Vianna M., Fonseca, D. B. &amp; D'Incao, F. (2007) The pink-shrimp trawling bycatch in the northern coast of Sao Paulo, Brazil, with emphasis on crustaceans. Nauplius, 15 (2), 49 - 55." type="journal article" year="2007">
Keunecke 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFADFFF3FBE4AA3B81ACFA8A" box="[401,457,1364,1390]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
). Sequences accession number (GenBank): CCDB 4172—16S (
<accessionNumber id="7382DEE8FFADFFF3FEA2AA3A853CFA8A" box="[1239,1369,1364,1390]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MF490149" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">MF490149</accessionNumber>
), COI (
<accessionNumber id="7382DEE8FFADFFF3FAEAAA16817AFA77" box="[159,287,1400,1427]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MF490046" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">MF490046</accessionNumber>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFADFFF3FB40AA168256FA76" author="Mantelatto, F. L. &amp; Terossi, M. &amp; Negri, M. &amp; Buranelli, R. C. &amp; Robles, R. &amp; Magalhaes, T. &amp; Tamburus, A. F. &amp; Rossi, N. &amp; Miyazaki, M. J." box="[309,563,1400,1426]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="805 - 815" refId="ref68637" refString="Mantelatto, F. L., Terossi, M., Negri, M., Buranelli, R. C., Robles, R., Magalhaes, T., Tamburus, A. F., Rossi, N. &amp; Miyazaki, M. J. (2018) DNA sequence database as a tool to identify decapod crustaceans on the Sao Paulo coastline. Mitochondrial DNA Part A: DNA Mapping, Sequencing and Analysis, 29 (5), 805 - 815. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 24701394.2017.1365848" type="journal article" year="2018">
Mantelatto 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFADFFF3FBC2AA17818AFA76" box="[439,495,1400,1426]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6C6E430BFFADFFF3FAE2AA8A823FFA1A" blockId="25.[151,602,1508,1534]" box="[151,602,1508,1534]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFADFFF3FAE2AA8A823FFA1A" bold="true" box="[151,602,1508,1534]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
